ratings.rComments: easiest A possible. gives tons of extra credit, but the professor herself is super unapproachable.
FSHN120 is the easiest class on the UIUC campus

Very easy class and actually pretty interesting. Dr. Roach can be super mean though. Even though only like 50 out of 750 people showed up to lecture she would freak out if someone came in late or stood in the back. Don't go to lecture. Take the quizzes a lot and do well on the projects. Easiest A you'll have here.

I'm writing this review 10 minutes after she made me feel like an idiot when I asked her a simple question about the nutritional analysis project. I showed her a question on my phone from the project and explained my question while I was showing it to her and all she said was "ask me a question, don't show me a screen" SUPER un-approachable.
This class is a joke. Go to the first lecture. Then stop. So easy it hurts. Literally just search the quiz questions on google and then memorize those for the exam. wow.

The class is basically a joke. SImply take a couple hours taking the practice tests since she just reuses those questions on the actual test. One test is dropped, which can be the final. Projects take some time, but are fairly simple.
Grades were based off of 4 exams and a final (one of which is dropped), 2 projects, and journal entries. Abundant extra credit opportunities. Easy A

Attendance is far from mandatory. Class is boring and the professor is a very dry lecturer. She reads word for word from the PowerPoint. Tests are based off of online quizzes that you can take endless times. The NAP projects are more work than they should be, but not overly difficult.

This class is very easy. Regular attendance is not necessary because all her power points and quizzes are on Compass.Just do well on her online quizzes and you should do well on her exams. She also drops your lowest exam score!Take it!!!

Not necessary to go to class. I would finish the tests in 5-10 minutes because it's all memorizing the quizzes she posts online for practice. Do good on the project. Lots of extra credit. Basically guaranteed an A.
This class is memorization- all i did to study for the exams was memorized the online practice quiz questions. Take the class if you are good at remembering

This is a very easy A class. Attendance is not mandatory. Take the online quizzes repeatedly because all of the exam questions come from the online quizzes. There is one project - NAP - that requires a bit of time but not hard at all.
Easy A.. All of her test answers come from the online quizes. The final is a joke and you dont have to go to class.. Take it
Roach is a heartless, evil, bitter woman. she is boring in lectures, but thank god it wasn't mandatory.

i suppose this class is just easy for someone. definitely not for me. i have no idea how are we supposed to know all those small details and those specific conditions about nutrition. many of them are not even mentioned in class. btw Roach is one of the most boring teacher on campus

Worst class ever. There is too much work involved for just a GenEd. Not easy. I don't know how people think it is. The NAP is a pain, especially since the website can shut down & Roach still penalized those students. She tries to make this a "college" course where you have more freedom, but that isn't true. Worst teacher and class ever.

This is by far the worst teacher I have ever had. She's the most unreasonable and crazy one ever. After her class, I literally went into a depression mode for 2 months and had to go to the hospital. I can't believe such a terrible human being could become a teacher. I think she should stop teaching to stop ruining and destroying people's lives.
No Comments.
This final was SO EASY! Just all exam questions from that semester in one. This is an easy class, just requires a lot of work (quizzes, NAPs, journal entries)
My easiest class at U of I so far.  Just give a reasonable amount of effort on the NAP project, study quiz questions, and you will be guaranteed an A.

Attendance is not mandatory in her lecture! Her class has extremely FAIR expectations. You take your quizzes online, and she has a bunch of extra credit opportunities also. Her exams are the exact same questions as the quiz questions.. if you memorize and understand those you will get an A on the exams!

This class is not an easy A by any means... you have to do the NAP really well and all the extra credit to secure an A... DO NOT BUY THE TEXTBOOK! its a waste of money. Also, don't go to lecture either just read her lecture outlines and the quizzes cause thats where she gets the test questions. she took attendance 1 time so dont go its not worth it

Easy class. Exchange quizzes with classmates b/c the exam questions come mainly from the quizzes. Lots of points in the class. 2 big projects. Journal responses every week about a topic you've covered in class-easy.

everyone always says postive things about this class but I dont agree. lectures are pointless. projects are long and tedious. journals once a week. 6 quizzes online due a couple days before the test. My advise is to only study of of the quizzes for the test, i mad the mistake of reading the book and she uses the quiz questions for test questions

This class was EASY but it's not a free A. Spend a few hours on the projects and tests- that's all you need. And she offered lots of easy EC. It was the easiest class I've ever had. The material was interesting & she explains things well. I took it during summer session 1 & she took attendance, just a heads up if you want to take it during summer.

One of the easiest and most interesting classes I've taken so far. You don't need to read the book or attend class, just read the outline she provides and the quiz questions before the exams and you'll get an A for sure.

I was there when she slammed her chair down and gave a hissy fit.  She is a pretty immature professor and can be pretty harsh, but the class is very easy.  I did not attend class for 3 weeks and got 96% on the exam. It is worth taking to help your GPA. The NAP is easy as well.  I did it the night before and A+.

sure this is a blowoff class, but that NAP project sure was consuming. I just have a story about her personality: when a few people in the 700-person class were talking, she stared at us all for 5 minutes, slammed a folding chair down on stage, stared and watched us before saying "If i deduct test points, will that shut ya up?" ..grow up Roach...

EASIEST CLASS ON CAMPUS!  You don't ever have to go to lecture as long as you do well on the quizzes and tests.  You're given 2 chances for the quizzes and they are ridiculously easy!  The tests are a cake walk.  There is no excuse to not get an A in this class.

BECKY is the best!  EASY A EASY A EASY A EASY A EASY A EASY A EASY A!  LOL at the guy who lied saying he spent 5 hours everyday studying for the exams!  You can only get A, B, C.  There are no +,- in this class : )

The NAPs are easy. The quizzes are time-consuming as you have to look in the book for most questions. Gather as many quiz questions as you can to study from because the exam is mostly the same questions. Easy A is you spend a few hours to study the quizzes and slides. Go to class for easy E.C. when it says so in the syllabus. She's pretty helpful.
the teacher is so harsh. don't listen to people who say this class is easy. I spent 5 hours everyday studying for this class and ended up with a C+. DONT TAKE THIS CLASS!!

Easy class, but alot of work required for a blowoff class. GREAT ADVICE:!!! IF YOU NEED TO TAKE THE OPTIONAL FINAL, MAKE SURE TO GO INTO OFFICE HOURS TO COPY PREVIOUS EXAMS. HER FINAL HAS THE SAME EXACT QUESTIONS AS PREVIOUS EXAMS.
This class has got to be one of the easiest on campus; there is no excuse for a B.

WOW!  What an easy class... I didn't even need to take the last exam to get an A.  MAD amounts of extra credit.  I really don't see how anybody doesn't get an A.  Interesting and useful material as well.  Honestly, this class would be better if it wasn't SOOO ridiculously easy.

This class was very interesting. The exams are easy if you study the lecture notes & outlines. Sometimes test/quiz questions are worded so that they are more confusing. An A is possible if you go to class & study a little bit for the exams. I don't ever use my textbook. Becky is very helpful at office hours.

Such an easy class. Skip lecture if you desire, it won't matter since the slides are online. There is a lot of extra credit. Numerous questions on the exams are exactly the same as those on the quizzes. There are 4 exams in addition to the final, which is annoying. However, you can drop the lowest. Do well on the four exams, then skip the final!
EASY CLASS!!! if you read the lecture notes you will do fine on the test. there is so much extra credit. this might be the easiest class on campus, no joke. take this class!!!!!!!!!!!
Easy A if you study for the tests. I thought lecture was boring and never went. She is very picky about details on the nutrition project!

I recommend this class to everyone! Becky is the best professor--great lecturer, so interested in the material she is teaching, very nice, and helpful. The class is not hard and the material is interesting and is helpful in real life.
Pretty boring class that I only went to a few times, but still managed to do well. Roach is rather annoying, but you really don't have to deal with her much.

The class was extremely easy; I probably attended the lecture 3 times and still recieved an A. However, I could not physically hand in my project due to an emergency and she did not understand. She deducted 10% off the project grade even after she receieved my emergency dean note. I'd still take the class, even if the roach is teaching it.

I recommend this class to everyone. It is very interesting and not hard at all. Becky is such a nice person and is so interested to teach the material, which makes going to class enjoyable. She offers a lot of extra credit and is just sooo nice!
Easiest class ever and also very interesting. If you need a science course and want an easy A this is something you should take. Lots of extra credit is also offered.
Not as easy as everyone says.  Dont go to class.  Read the book and slides online.  Do all the extra credit.
Not as easy as everyone says, but an interesting class.  She is very fair.  Read book.

Some parts of this class were intersting.  Lectures not being one of them. Class notes are posted online.  Lots of memorizing required. Easy to get an A if you are willing to memorize alll the vitamins and minerals and stuff like that.
soft spoken-Its difficult to hear her in Follinger.  The tests are okay, but they require some studying.  She puts all the notes online.
a lot of online resources provided. a lot of memorizing required.

It was very easy to get an A, but the class is really boring because Roach is boring.  I regret going to class as often as I went, could have not gone so often and just cramped the notes the night before the test and been just fine.  Easy A and a life science gen-ed.
Not as easy as I thought it would be. I never went to lecture and it screwed me over for all the exams. She doesn't really know what she's talking about.

When I took this class in Fall 04, it was SUPER easy. NEVER went to lecture, NEVER took notes, and only showed up for the scheduled exams. I finished the class with an 86. The following semester, my roommate took it with Roach and it's more work than before, but still easy.

All lecture notes are posted online, so there is no need to go to class.  Very nit-picky quizzes are given that can be confusing.  All in all, a class you don't need to show up for except to take exams, so it is easy enough.
very easy. but lectures are really boring. it was hard to stay motivated and keep going. basically reads from the lecture notes which are posted online. easy science gen ed.

Easiest A! I didn't need to take the final. If you go to lecture you will never need to open your book or study for a single moment. The information is basic. She is focused on communicating the main ideas of nutrition, not grilling students with trivial facts.
No Comments
